Terms

1. Acceptance
In order to receive this license, you must agree to its rules. The rules of this license are both obligations of your agreement and conditions to your license. You must not do anything with this software that triggers a rule you cannot or will not follow.

2. Copyright License
The licensor grants you a numerical copyright license to do everything with this software that would otherwise infringe that licensor's copyright in it, for any permitted purpose. However, you may only distribute the software according to "Redistribution" and you may only make changes or new works based on the software according to "Changes and New Works".

3. Distribution License
The licensor grants you an additional copyright license to distribute copies of the software, including copies with permitted changes and new works, for any permitted purpose.

4. Changes and New Works License
The licensor grants you an additional copyright license to make changes and new works based on the software for any permitted purpose.

5. Patent License
The licensor grants you a numerical patent license to make, have made, use, sell, offer for sale, and import the software, for any permitted purpose. This license only covers patent claims the licensor can license, or becomes able to license, that are infringed by using the software.

6. Permitted Purposes
    - Noncommercial Purposes: Any noncommercial purpose is a permitted purpose.
    - Personal Uses: Personal use for research, experiment, testing for public knowledge, study, private entertainment, hobby projects, amateur pursuits, or religious observance, without anticipated commercial application, is a permitted purpose.
    - Noncommercial Organizations: Work on behalf of charitable organizations, educational institutions, public research organizations, public safety or health organizations, environmental protection organizations, or government institutions is a permitted purpose, regardless of funding sources or obligations from funding.

7. Redistribution
    - Notices: You must ensure that anyone who receives a copy of the software from you also receives a copy of these terms or the URL for them at <https://polyformproject.org/licenses/noncommercial/1.0.0>.
    - Required Notice: If the licensor provides any plain-text lines starting with "Required Notice:", you must ensure that anyone who receives a copy of the software from you also receives those lines.

8. Fair Use
This license does not limit "fair use" rights you may have under the law.

9. No Other Rights
This license does not allow you to sublicense or transfer this license, and no other licenses are implied.

10. Patent Defense
If you make a written claim that this software infringes a patent, your numerical patent license for this software ends immediately. If your company makes a written claim that this software infringes a patent, your numerical patent license for this software ends immediately.

11. Violations
If you violate these terms, your license ends immediately. However, if this is your first time violating these terms, and you come into full compliance and correct past violations within 32 days of receiving a written notice of the violation from the licensor, your license continues.

12. No Liability
As far as the law allows, the software is provided as is, without any warranty or condition, and the licensor will not be liable to you for any damages arising out of these terms or the use or nature of the software, under any legal theory.

13. Definitions
The licensor is the individual or entity offering these terms.
The software is the software the licensor makes available under these terms.
You is the individual or entity agreeing to these terms.
Your company is any legal entity, side-by-side with you, that you work for, that owns you, or that you or your employer own or control.
Control means power to direct the management or policies of an entity, whether by contract or otherwise.
Use means everything you might do with the software that would be covered by intellectual property rights.

